Comment: 0,0:48:57.78,0:49:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,~~~ BEGIN REAL AFTERLIVE AFTERTALK ~~~
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.28,0:49:00.78,Ena,,0,0,0,,Thanks so much everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.28,0:49:00.78,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Thanks so much everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.78,0:49:05.48,Ena,,0,0,0,,The Afterlive was so good, wasn't it? The song too of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.48,0:49:14.35,Ena,,0,0,0,,That and the talk segments, I was so glad to see everything getting back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.35,0:49:17.45,Ena,,0,0,0,,Thanks for watching with us, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.28,0:49:17.45,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.45,0:49:25.12,Ena,,0,0,0,,So that was the first Afterlive performance of "Yoka ni Mitorete",
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.12,0:49:28.45,Ena,,0,0,0,,so I think there may be a few first-time listeners here,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.45,0:49:36.52,Ena,,0,0,0,,as well as maybe some who've already seen the 2D and 3D MVs that've been out since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.52,0:49:40.72,Ena,,0,0,0,,Come on. It's just so good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.72,0:49:44.98,Ena,,0,0,0,,Just simply a wonderful song.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.98,0:49:51.18,Ena,,0,0,0,,"Yoka ni Mitorete"... For Ena, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.18,0:49:56.38,Ena,,0,0,0,,this song represents the words she's facing Mizuki and saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.38,0:50:02.55,Ena,,0,0,0,,Like the lyrics say, she's just holding onto Mizuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.55,0:50:06.18,Ena,,0,0,0,,Holding onto Mizuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.18,0:50:10.38,Ena,,0,0,0,,so gently, and on the verge of tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.38,0:50:19.25,Ena,,0,0,0,,N25 songs often have lots of painful or negative emotions in their lyrics,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.25,0:50:23.78,Ena,,0,0,0,,but now that everyone is moving forward little by little in their own journeys,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.78,0:50:27.58,Ena,,0,0,0,,they can voice more than just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.58,0:50:31.62,Ena,,0,0,0,,That's why they could sing this song.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.62,0:50:39.28,Ena,,0,0,0,,So actually, keeno-san was able to participate remotely in our recording sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.28,0:50:49.45,Ena,,0,0,0,,They supported each of us in our four recording sessions by voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.45,0:50:56.22,Ena,,0,0,0,,But weren't they such a warm and gentle person, just like their song?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.22,0:51:02.55,Ena,,0,0,0,,I thought, "Makes sense that such a gentle person was able to make such a gentle song."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.55,0:51:07.88,Ena,,0,0,0,,And then we were able to watch the 2DMV and 3DMV for the first time yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.88,0:51:17.15,Ena,,0,0,0,,We were able to see Bouno-san's wonderful illustrations in so many different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.15,0:51:23.95,Ena,,0,0,0,,You can really tell how much respect for the story they put in the MVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.95,0:51:28.08,Ena,,0,0,0,,Please do watch them, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.75,0:51:28.08,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Please watch to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.08,0:51:29.42,Ena,,0,0,0,,They're both flower-themed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.42,0:51:29.95,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,They are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.95,0:51:31.15,Ena,,0,0,0,,"Yoka ni Mitorete",
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.95,0:51:31.15,Ruby Text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960.381,960)}"Admiring the Late-Blooming Flowers"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.15,0:51:33.02,Ena,,0,0,0,,and "Bake no Hana."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.15,0:51:33.02,Ruby Text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1007,960)}"Monstrous Flower"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.02,0:51:36.98,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,During our recording sessions, we asked if they coordinated that,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.98,0:51:41.25,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,but it was actually completely unplanned that both titles would have the word "flower".
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.25,0:51:47.88,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,We always provide a— what is it— a story prototype with basic details to the vocaloid producers,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.88,0:51:52.52,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,and both ended up coming up with a song about "flowers".
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.52,0:51:55.28,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,I think that was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.28,0:51:56.22,Ena,,0,0,0,,Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.22,0:52:00.15,Ena,,0,0,0,,They didn't connect the titles like that on purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.15,0:52:03.45,Ena,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's a reason for it, but it's not like they coordinated this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.45,0:52:04.52,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Complete coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.52,0:52:07.05,Ena,,0,0,0,,It felt like it was almost a fated coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.05,0:52:10.32,Ena,,0,0,0,,One that made a wonderfully connected story.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.32,0:52:15.98,Ena,,0,0,0,,We got so much reaction to "Bake no Hana" too.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.98,0:52:20.75,Ena,,0,0,0,,Even the singing distribution was— how to say—
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.75,0:52:24.68,Ena,,0,0,0,,it reminds you a lot of the story, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.68,0:52:28.88,Ena,,0,0,0,,Even the fact that Ena has relatively few parts might have some grounding there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.88,0:52:31.28,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,It did, didn't it? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.52,0:52:31.28,Ena,,0,0,0,,It did.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.28,0:52:35.95,Ena,,0,0,0,,Please, do listen to both songs if you haven't already.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.89,0:52:35.95,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Please do listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.95,0:52:47.05,Ena,,0,0,0,,So once again, both the 2DMV and the 3DMV are available to watch here on the official ProSeka YouTube channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.05,0:52:52.15,Ena,,0,0,0,,so maybe after this Aftertalk, please watch as many times as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.15,0:52:56.35,Ena,,0,0,0,,Both are really good in their own ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.35,0:52:59.65,Ena,,0,0,0,,So please do if you have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.65,0:53:00.45,Ena,,0,0,0,,Moving on!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.45,0:53:09.08,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Alright then, we also have 5 new cards to introduce as well today.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.08,0:53:13.05,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Have you already seen the card art and side stories, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.05,0:53:14.18,Ena,,0,0,0,,Alright...
